{
  "texts": [
    "The two mixtures were then combined, thoroughly mixed, and incubated at RT for 15 min before being dropwise applied to the HEK293T cells.",
    "The virus particles were collected 24 hours and 48 hours after transfection and concentrated with Lenti-X™ Concentrator (Takara, California, USA, Cat#631232).",
    "The pellets were then resuspended with PBS, aliquoted, and stored at -80 °C.",
    "The iPSCs were infected with the lentivirus, and positive clones were selected by bioluminescence imaging (BLI) with IVIS Lumina II In Vivo Imaging system (PerkinElmer, Waltham, USA).",
    "Ten Luc2 positive clones were pooled to maximize the labeling rate and minimize the colony effect."
  ]
}